								Currently, Kalyan Mathrusangham (KMS) has over 6500 mothers as members, and they
								collaborate closely with other organizations at the parish, zonal, and diocese levels.
								Mathrusangam aims to provide support and encouragement to mothers within the church
								community. They offer a platform for mothers to connect, share experiences, and uplift
								one another in their journey of motherhood.
								<br><br>
								Their primary objective is to deepen their faith, provide spiritual guidance, and equip
								them to be godly mothers and role models. The members of Mathrusangam solely organize
								the feasts of MotherMary especially 'Mathavinte Vanakkamasam' in the month of May.
								Additionally, they take part in a variety of diocesan activities like group singing,
								mime, bible quizzes, etc., which allows them to witness Christ through their deeds.
								<br><br>
								The association recognizes the unique challenges and joys of motherhood and seeks to
